data.value:
Mt. Naupa: Beautiful, Beginner-Friendly Mountain Peak in Naga City Steep mountains and ranges with an elevation of more than 2,500 meters above sea level hold in its peaks a natural phenomenon that many travelers and mountain hikers look forward to – the sea of clouds.
Luckily for Sugboanons, one of the many mountains in the island allows for anyone to experience the breathtaking sea of clouds regardless of gear or experience. All they need are a few gears and the excitement to witness the sea of clouds.
Mt. Naupa is a mountain with an almost-perfect cone and stands as the highest peak in Naga. It stands at only around 587 meters above sea level. Despite being barely 1000 meters above sea level, the mountain occasionally has a sea of clouds. With Mt. Naupa being one of the most accessible mountains in Cebu, this also makes it the most accessible viewing point to witness a sea of clouds.
